  "original_title": "\u0bb0\u0bc2.1.78 \u0b95\u0bcb\u0b9f\u0bbf\u0baf\u0bc8 \u0b89\u0b9f\u0ba9\u0bcd \u0b95\u0bc8\u0baf\u0bb3\u0bbf\u0b95\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bb5\u0bc1\u0bae\u0bcd",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Hand over Rs.1.78 crores",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "Yesterday (28), Fort Magistrate Dilina Gamage ordered the Fort Police Station Officer-in-Charge to immediately hand over the 17.8 million (1.78 crore) rupees seized and handed over to the court by the protesters who seized the Presidential Palace.",
        "The Fort Police informed the forum that on July 9, 17.8 million rupees were handed over from the President's House by the protestors.",
        "The judge ordered the money to be handed over to the court immediately, saying that despite three weeks having passed since the money was handed over to the police, no report in this regard has been submitted to the court.",
        "Apart from that, the judge directed the officer-in-charge of the Fort police station to submit a statement regarding the money.",
        "In addition, the judge also ordered the release of the four persons who were arrested on charges of illegal entry into the Presidential Palace on July 9th, on bail of 5 lakh rupees.",
        "It is noteworthy that the report submitted by the police to the court indicated that the four suspects were among those who were counting the money at the Presidential Palace."
      ],
